<taxonomicName LSID="BE744BDE-EFE1-5BCA-B9AA-8753E587D3CF" authority="D. R. Hunt, Kew Bull. 35 (2): 441. 1980." authorityName="D. R. Hunt, Kew Bull. 35 (2): 441. 1980." class="Liliopsida" family="Commelinaceae" genus="Tradescantia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tradescantia subsp. sect." order="Commelinales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Mandonia" species="zanonia" subSpecies="sect.">Tradescantia sect. Mandonia D.R.Hunt, Kew Bull. 35(2): 441. 1980.</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
The section is characterized by perennial herbs, with tuberous roots, definite base, without rhizomes, leaves with symmetric or slightly asymmetric base, inflorescences mainly axillary, sessile, cincinni bracts much reduced or rarely leaf-like in the terminal inflorescences, bracteoles inconspicuous, flowers flat, rarely tubular, sepals equal, free, not keeled, petals free, sessile, stamens 6 and equal, free or epipetalous, filaments coiling at post anthesis, medially sparsely bearded with moniliform hairs, connectives quadrangular to rectangular, rarely rhomboid, anther sacs C-shaped, ovary pubescent, stigma truncate to capitulate, seeds scrobiculate to rugose, rarely costate, embryotega conspicuous and dorsal (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4114596" author="Hunt, DR" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="437 - 422" refId="B20" refString="Hunt, DR, 1980. Sections and series in Tradescantia - American Commelinaceae: IX. Kew Bulletin 35 (2): 437 - 422, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/4114596" title="Sections and series in Tradescantia - American Commelinaceae: IX." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4114596" volume="35" year="1980">Hunt 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" author="Pellegrini, MOO" journalOrPublisher="Instituto de Biologia, Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refId="B29" refString="Pellegrini, MOO, 2015. Filogenia e revisao taxonomica de Tradescantia L. sect. Austrotradescantia D.R.Hunt (Commelinaceae). In: MsC thesis. Instituto de Biologia, Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, DOI: https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" title="Filogenia e revisao taxonomica de Tradescantia L. sect. Austrotradescantia D. R. Hunt (Commelinaceae)" url="https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" volumeTitle="MsC thesis." year="2015">Pellegrini 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<pageBreakToken pageId="9" pageNumber="10" start="start">Comments</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Commelinaceae" genus="Tradescantia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tradescantia subsp. sect." order="Commelinales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Mandonia" species="zanonia" subSpecies="sect.">Tradescantia sect. Mandonia</taxonomicName>
is a poorly understood group, currently represented by 12 species (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4114596" author="Hunt, DR" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="437 - 422" refId="B20" refString="Hunt, DR, 1980. Sections and series in Tradescantia - American Commelinaceae: IX. Kew Bulletin 35 (2): 437 - 422, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/4114596" title="Sections and series in Tradescantia - American Commelinaceae: IX." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4114596" volume="35" year="1980">Hunt 1980</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4102949" author="Hunt, DR" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination=": 406" refId="B22" refString="Hunt, DR, 1986b. New names and a new species in Tradescantia - American Commelinaceae: XIV. Kew Bulletin 41 (2): 406, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/4102949" title="New names and a new species in Tradescantia - American Commelinaceae: XIV" url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4102949" volume="41" year="1986 b">1986b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hunt, DR" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="141 - 142" refId="B23" refString="Hunt, DR, 2007. A new species of Tradescantia (Commelinaceae) from Mexico. Kew Bulletin 62 (1): 141 - 142" title="A new species of Tradescantia (Commelinaceae) from Mexico." volume="62" year="2007">2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/3393009" author="Grant, JR" journalOrPublisher="Novon" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="117 - 123" refId="B12" refString="Grant, JR, 2000. New Mesoamerican species of Dichorisandra and Tradescantia section Mandonia (Commelinaceae). Novon 10 (2): 117 - 123, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/3393009" title="New Mesoamerican species of Dichorisandra and Tradescantia section Mandonia (Commelinaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/3393009" volume="10" year="2000">Grant 2000</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Grant, JR" journalOrPublisher="Novon" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="299 - 300" refId="B13" refString="Grant, JR, 2004. Tradescantia boliviana (Commelinaceae), a new combination for an overlooked South American species. Novon 14 (3): 299 - 300" title="Tradescantia boliviana (Commelinaceae), a new combination for an overlooked South American species." volume="14" year="2004">2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Zamudio, S" journalOrPublisher="Acta Botanica Mexicana" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="25 - 30" refId="B44" refString="Zamudio, S, Espejo-Serna, A, Lopez-Ferrari, AR, Ceja-Romero, J, 2013. Una nueva especie de Tradescantia (Commelinaceae) del estado de Queretaro, Mexico. Acta Botanica Mexicana 102: 25 - 30" title="Una nueva especie de Tradescantia (Commelinaceae) del estado de Queretaro, Mexico." volume="102" year="2013">Zamudio et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
). This section possesses a very interesting disjunctive distribution, being restricted to Seasonally Dry Tropical Forests throughout the Neotropics. Species delimitation is especially complicated in this this group, due to great vegetative plasticity within species, and conserved reproductive features. Most species can be easily identified based on their allopatric distributions, but hardly differentiated based solely on their morphological features (Pellegrini, unpublished data). In South America, 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. subsp. sect." pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="section" section="Mandonia" species="zanonia" subSpecies="sect.">T. sect. Mandonia</taxonomicName>
is currently represented exclusively by two species, 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. ambigua" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species" species="ambigua">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">T. ambigua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Mart. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">ex</emphasis>
Schult. &amp; Schult.f. and 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. boliviana" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species" species="boliviana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">T. boliviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Commelinaceae" genus="Tradescantia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tradescantia boliviana" order="Commelinales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="boliviana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Tradescantia boliviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has hitherto been considered exclusive to Argentina, Bolivia, Paraguay, and Peru (
<bibRefCitation author="Grant, JR" journalOrPublisher="Novon" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="299 - 300" refId="B13" refString="Grant, JR, 2004. Tradescantia boliviana (Commelinaceae), a new combination for an overlooked South American species. Novon 14 (3): 299 - 300" title="Tradescantia boliviana (Commelinaceae), a new combination for an overlooked South American species." volume="14" year="2004">Grant 2004</bibRefCitation>
). However, after analyzing several herbaria we came across specimens representing 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. boliviana" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species" species="boliviana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">T. boliviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that reached the Brazilian territory, in the state of Mato Grosso do Sul. Thus, we present an identification key differentiating both species, illustrations, a distribution map, and the needed comments and typifications.
</paragraph>
